{
  "texts": [
    "Disclaimer: Restrictions on dimensions of operators and 't Hooft anomaliesThroughout this paper, 1.",
    "We consider action of (p) only on operators of co-dimension at least 2.2.",
    "We allow (p) to have a 't Hooft anomaly associated to an element of H d+1 (B (p), ×), where B (p) denotes the classifying space of (p).Both these assumptions go hand in hand.",
    "The above type of 't Hooft anomaly is localized only on points, and so does not affect the action of (p) on untwisted sector operators of co-dimension at least 2.",
    "Thus, while discussing the action of (p) on operators of these co-dimensions, we can effectively forget about the anomaly."
  ]
}